{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769630353,"nonce":"OzGMSzKpDTSEUY+2wC8Ha99OOAc=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mf_xj","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/112","origin":"github"},"title":"Suppress vcstool pkg_resources deprecation warnings in status output","message":"## Problem\n\nThe `status_report.sh` script shows multiple deprecation warnings from vcstool, polluting the output:\n\n```\n/usr/bin/vcs:6: DeprecationWarning: pkg_resources is deprecated as an API.\n  See https://setuptools.pypa.io/en/latest/pkg_resources.html\n  from pkg_resources import load_entry_point\n```\n\nThis warning appears **6 times** (once per workspace layer), making the output harder to read.\n\n**Impact**:\n- Visual noise in status reports\n- Harder to quickly scan for actual issues\n- May confuse users/agents about workspace health\n- Not actionable (upstream vcstool issue)\n\n## Root Cause\n\nVcstool uses deprecated `pkg_resources` API. This is an upstream issue in vcstool, not something we can fix directly.\n\n**Upstream tracking**: \n- Related to Python packaging migration from pkg_resources → importlib.metadata\n- Vcstool would need to update its import mechanism\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### Option 1: Suppress stderr in status_report.sh (Recommended)\n```bash\n# Suppress Python warnings for vcs commands\nexport PYTHONWARNINGS=\"ignore::DeprecationWarning\"\nvcs status workspaces/core_ws 2\u003e/dev/null || vcs status workspaces/core_ws\n```\n\n### Option 2: Filter warnings with grep\n```bash\nvcs status workspaces/core_ws 2\u003e\u00261 | grep -v \"DeprecationWarning\" | grep -v \"pkg_resources\"\n```\n\n### Option 3: Wrapper script\n```bash\n# .agent/scripts/vcs_quiet.sh\nPYTHONWARNINGS=\"ignore::DeprecationWarning\" vcs \"$@\"\n```\n\nThen use:\n```bash\nvcs_quiet.sh status workspaces/core_ws\n```\n\n## Implementation\n\n**Recommended**: Option 1 (simplest)\n\nUpdate `status_report.sh`:\n```bash\n# Near top of script, before any vcs calls\nexport PYTHONWARNINGS=\"ignore::DeprecationWarning\"\n```\n\n**Files to update**:\n- `.agent/scripts/status_report.sh`\n- Any other scripts calling `vcs` directly\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `status_report.sh` output shows no deprecation warnings\n- [ ] Actual vcs errors/warnings still visible\n- [ ] Works across all workspace layers\n- [ ] No functional changes to vcs behavior\n\n## Notes\n\n- This is a **cosmetic** fix, not a functional bug\n- The deprecation warning doesn't affect vcstool functionality\n- Upstream vcstool fix would be ideal, but outside our control\n- Suppressing the warning is safe since we can't act on it anyway\n\n## Priority\n\n**Low** - Cosmetic improvement, doesn't affect functionality.\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Claude Sonnet 4.5`","files":null}]}